      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugin-runtime): restore channel turn alias",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Restores the deprecated `core.channel.turn.*` runtime surface as an alias of `core.channel.inbound.*` for shipped channel plugins compiled before the inbound rename.\n- Keeps the alias as the same object as `inbound`, so there is no second implementation path or drift in production runtime behavior.\n- Updates the PluginRuntime type, plugin runtime mock, API baseline hash, and SDK docs to describe the compatibility alias while keeping new plugin guidance on `inbound.*`.\n- Intentionally does not change bundled Feishu source, channel logic, config, or package artifacts.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses #91122\n\nRelated #91122\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner? No direct maintainer request; this is a focused compatibility fix for the reported shipped plugin runtime break.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\nBehavior addressed: Restores `runtime.channel.turn.*` / `core.channel.turn.*` as a deprecated compatibility alias for old channel plugins while preserving `runtime.channel.inbound.*` as the canonical API.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS, Node 24-compatible repo toolchain, branch `fix/91122-runtime-channel-turn-alias` after this patch.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Built the runtime, then ran this Node probe against the generated `dist/runtime-channel-UUbgZd8n.js` chunk:\n\n```console\n$ node --input-type=module - <<'NODE'\nimport { createRuntimeChannel } from './dist/runtime-channel-UUbgZd8n.js';\nconst channel = createRuntimeChannel({\n  providerControl: {},\n  createUnifiedProviderSetup: () => ({}),\n  ensureRuntimeAuthDeps: () => ({}),\n  runtimeAdapters: {},\n  createAgentStateDB: () => ({}),\n  createAgentStateDBForStorePath: () => ({}),\n  registerInboundSession: () => {},\n  runWithDispatch: () => {},\n});\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({\n  hasTurn: Boolean(channel.turn),\n  sameObject: channel.turn === channel.inbound,\n  sameRun: channel.turn.run === channel.inbound.run,\n  sameBuildContext: channel.turn.buildContext === channel.inbound.buildContext,\n  sameDispatchReply: channel.turn.dispatchReply === channel.inbound.dispatchReply,\n  sameRunPreparedReply: channel.turn.runPreparedReply === channel.inbound.runPreparedReply,\n}));\nNODE\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```console\n{\"hasTurn\":true,\"sameObject\":true,\"sameRun\":true,\"sameBuildContext\":true,\"sameDispatchReply\":true,\"sameRunPreparedReply\":true}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The built runtime exposes `channel.turn`; `channel.turn === channel.inbound`; all four legacy functions are the same function references as the canonical inbound runtime helpers.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not install `openclaw@2026.6.x` with `@openclaw/feishu@2026.5.28` or run a live Feishu DM against real credentials.\n\nProof limitations or environment constraints: The proof validates the exact built runtime compatibility surface that old compiled plugins dereference. It does not prove a full Feishu WebSocket setup because that requires live Feishu credentials and an older published plugin install.\n\nBefore evidence (optional but encouraged): Issue #91122 reports old plugins failing on `core.channel.turn.run()` because the runtime only exposed `channel.inbound.*`.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nCommands run:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/runtime/runtime-channel.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=.artifacts/vitest-cache-91122 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:gen`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:strict-smoke`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/plugins/runtime/types-channel.ts src/plugins/runtime/runtime-channel.ts src/plugins/runtime/runtime-channel.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.ts src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/ui.js build`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nRegression coverage added or updated:\n\n- `src/plugins/runtime/runtime-channel.test.ts` now asserts deprecated `channel.turn` is wired to `channel.inbound` with object/function identity.\n- `src/plugin-sdk/test-helpers/plugin-runtime-mock.test.ts` now asserts the test helper exposes the same alias and that inbound overrides are visible through `turn`.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known:\n\n- Old compiled plugins calling `core.channel.turn.run()` could dereference `undefined.run` after the runtime rename removed the `turn` key.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\n- Tests were added for the runtime surface and the SDK runtime mock.\n\nNotes:\n\n- A full `pnpm build` rerun reached `tsdown`, runtime postbuild, plugin SDK DTS generation, SDK export checks, and the final `ui:build` stage, then hit my 15 minute local command timeout before completion. I ran the final UI build stage separately with `node scripts/ui.js build`, which passed. An earlier full `pnpm build` completed successfully on this worktree before the final test-helper alias correction.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`) Yes, old shipped channel plugins can call the deprecated runtime alias again.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`) No.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`) No.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\n- Plugin runtime compatibility surface and SDK typing.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\n- The alias reuses the exact same object as `channel.inbound`, avoiding duplicate behavior.\n- Type/API baseline, focused runtime tests, plugin runtime mock tests, docs, DTS strict smoke, and autoreview all cover the changed surface.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\n- Ready for ClawSweeper and maintainer review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\n- CI and ClawSweeper review are pending after the latest branch and proof-body update. Full live Feishu old-plugin validation was not run locally.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\n- Local autoreview initially found that the plugin runtime mock used a separate `turn` object; I fixed it so overrides on `inbound` propagate through the alias. Final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\n",
